15 Sections 5-8 and 16-20 of this bill codify similar provisions into state law,
16 thereby requiring certain health facilities and providers of health care to take
17 reasonable steps to ensure that language barriers do not prevent a person with
18 limited English proficiency from obtaining necessary access to health care.
19 Sections 5, 16 and 20 prescribe certain factors for determining whether an action is
20 necessary for a health facility or provider of health care to be in compliance with
21 that requirement. Sections 5 and 16 require that a service to provide language
22 assistance be available free of charge, be accurate in translation or interpretation be
23 provided in a timely manner and protect the ability of the person with limited
24 English proficiency to make independent decisions. Sections 5 and 16 require that
25 a qualified translator review a machine-translated document under certain
26 circumstances.
27 Sections 5 and 16 require a health facility or provider of health care to use a
28 qualified interpreter or translator to provide interpreting or translating services, and
29 sections 8 and 19 establish the qualifications to serve as an interpreter or translator.
30 Sections 6 and 17 prohibit the use of an unqualified interpreter, except in certain
31 circumstances. Sections 6 and 17 also prohibit a health facility or provider of
32 health care from requiring a person with limited English proficiency to provide his
33 or her own interpreter or pay the cost of an interpreter. Sections 7 and 18 prescribe
34 requirements governing the use of a remote interpreter. Sections 3, 4 and 15 of this
35 bill define certain terms, and section 2 of this bill establishes the applicability of the
36 definitions set forth in sections 3 and 4. Sections 9 and 10 of this bill make
37 conforming changes to establish the applicability of certain provisions. Sections
38 11-13, 20 and 21 of this bill prescribe various mechanisms for the enforcement of
39 sections 5-8 and 16-19, including the imposition of administrative sanctions
40 against a health facility that fails to comply with those provisions and professional
41 discipline against a provider of health care who fails to comply with those
42 provisions.
